<body>
<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Bestow a Blessing</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">How to bless a person , group , place or thing .</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1006" relname="preparation">Figure out exactly who or what the blessing is going to be for .</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1006" relname="joint">Using names is always best .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1007" relname="span">Think about what attributes you want to create or enhance in the object of the blessing .</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1009" relname="joint">Traits such as peace , strength , courage , wit , kindness , grace , good looks , health , happiness , long life , justice , and prosperity are some possibilities .</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="9" relname="condition">If you &apos;re religious ,</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1011" relname="span">look at your scripture for ideas .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1013" relname="span">There might be a verse or quote</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1014" relname="contrast">you want to use ,</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1015" relname="span">or there may be pre-written blessings</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="12" relname="elaboration">you can recite .</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1016" relname="contrast">If you &apos;re not religious</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1017" relname="joint">or do n&apos;t want to do a religious-sounding blessing ,</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1018" relname="joint">look up some other kinds of quotes , especially poetry .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1019" relname="joint">Even songs .</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1021" relname="span">These can be inspirational</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="18" relname="concession">even if you choose to write your own blessing .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1023" relname="span">Compose the words of the blessing .</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1025" relname="contrast">You can write them down</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1025" relname="contrast">or memorize them ,</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1026" relname="span">but make sure you know what you &apos;re going to say</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="23" relname="circumstance">before you say it .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1028" relname="condition">Just as with a toast or a speech ,</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1028" relname="span">you do n&apos;t want to spoil it</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1029" relname="contrast">by forgetting the words</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1029" relname="contrast">or stumbling .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1031" relname="span">Keep it concise :</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1033" relname="span">it should n&apos;t take more than two minutes</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="30" relname="purpose">to say the whole thing ,</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1032" relname="joint">and preferably less time than that .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="34" relname="condition">If you want to ,</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1035" relname="span">you can include a ritual of any sort you like .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1037" relname="span">Try reading up on rituals , rites and superstitions</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="35" relname="purpose">to get some ideas .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1038" relname="span">Start with traditions from your own ancestry or ethnicity .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1040" relname="span">To bless a person ,</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="38" relname="elaboration">place your hand on his or her head .</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1043" relname="span">Traditionally the right hand ,</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="40" relname="elaboration">which in most people is stronger ,</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1044" relname="span">is the best one</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="42" relname="purpose">to use .</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="45" relname="condition">If touching is unacceptable ,</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1046" relname="span">hold your hand above the person .</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1047" relname="joint">Recite the blessing .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1048" relname="span">Have a drink or a special treat</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1049" relname="contrast">to celebrate ,</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1049" relname="contrast">or give the object of the blessing a gift .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1051" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1051" relname="joint">Do n&apos;t use the blessing as a lecture .</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1054" relname="span">You can also bless a house , a place of business , the food</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1055" relname="contrast">you eat ,</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1056" relname="span">or anything</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="54" relname="elaboration">you make with your hands .</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1058" relname="span">Different people have different ideas</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="56" relname="elaboration">of what a blessing actually does ;</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1059" relname="span">depending on your point of view ,</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1061" relname="span">it &apos;s a request to the higher Power</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="59" relname="purpose">to bestow the real gifts ,</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1062" relname="span">or it &apos;s an expression of your will with the hope</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="61" relname="elaboration">that what you want will become manifest .</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1051" relname="joint">Use phrases in the future tense , such as &quot; May you ...</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1065" relname="preparation">&quot;</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="66" relname="concession">A blessing does n&apos;t guarantee good things ,</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1066" relname="span">but it might help .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1068" relname="span">In some cultures , it &apos;s traditional to bless children</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="67" relname="circumstance">when they reach certain stages of life , or even on a regular basis .</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1065" relname="joint">Blessings can be public or private .</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1065" relname="joint">You can do it with a large audience or on your own .</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1072" relname="span">Invoke the attributes of people</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="71" relname="elaboration">you admire .</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1074" relname="span">You can compare the person</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1075" relname="span">you &apos;re blessing to somebody</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="74" relname="elaboration">who is already great .</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1065" relname="joint">Again , keep the words of your blessing short .</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1065" relname="joint">It &apos;s the thought</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1065" relname="joint">that counts .</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="1079" relname="preparation">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1080" relname="same_unit">Be smart</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1082" relname="circumstance">when you &apos;re composing the blessing ,</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="1082" relname="span">and word it</segment>
<segment id="83" parent="1083" relname="span">so that it wo n&apos;t offend the person</segment>
<segment id="84" parent="83" relname="elaboration">you &apos;re blessing or somebody watching .</segment>
<segment id="85" parent="1085" relname="condition">If in doubt ,</segment>
<segment id="86" parent="1085" relname="span">skip any mention of deities</segment>
<segment id="87" parent="86" relname="elaboration">( God or gods ) .</segment>
